==Classical Nahuatl==
===Alternative forms===
* {{l|nci|iautl}}
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|nci|/jaːˈoːtɬ/}}
* {{IPA|nci|[ˈjáːˈ.oːtɬ]}}
===Noun===
{{head|nci|noun|head=yāōtl}}
# [[enemy|Enemy]].
#* '''1555:''' [[w:Alonso de Molina|Alonso de Molina]], ''Aqui comienca vn vocabulario en la lengua Castellana y Mexicana''
#*: Enemigo. '''teyaouh'''.
====Usage notes====
As an element of compounds, '''yao-''' usually has the meaning "war; warfare" (see '''[[yaoyotl]]''').
